1) add websocket dependency
					<dependency>
					    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
					    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-websocket</artifactId>
					</dependency>
2) create webSocketConfig
3) create new controller (Notification Handler)
4) call the notificationHandler method in another method where notification is saved to database
5) update the notification using javascript


//For real-time updates across different computers, we need WebSocket, which allows bi-directional communication.